# Implementation Plan - Fix Startup Hang on Windows

The Paperclip dev server is getting stuck on Windows during the database migration phase. My research indicates that the embedded PostgreSQL instance is listening on the IPv6 loopback address (`[::1]`), while the application code is attempting to connect via the IPv4 loopback address (`127.0.0.1`). This mismatch can cause connections to hang or timeout.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Connection Logic

I will update the connection strings to use `localhost` instead of the hardcoded `127.0.0.1`. This allows the operating system and the database client to correctly resolve the available loopback interface (IPv4 or IPv6) and establish a successful connection.

#### [MODIFY] [migration-runtime.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/packages/db/src/migration-runtime.ts)
- Replace all occurrences of `127.0.0.1` with `localhost` in the embedded PostgreSQL connection strings.

